    "lockedSequence": true,
    "sections": [
      {
        "id": "welcome",
        "title": "Welcome and First Priorities",
        "order": 1,
        "estMin": 20,
        "lessons": [
          {
            "id": "mission-values",
            "title": "Mission, Values, and Culture",
            "order": 1,
            "estMin": 10,
            "continueMode": "guided",
            "blocks": [
              {
                "id": "intro",
                "type": "heading",
                "level": 2,
                "text": "Starting with clarity"
              },
              {
                "id": "body",
                "type": "text",
                "html": "<p>Every organization has a way of working. New employees should understand the mission, service standards, communication expectations, and behaviors that define professional success.</p><p>Culture is not only a statement on a wall. It is reflected in how people communicate, solve problems, serve customers, and support one another.</p>",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "callout",
                "type": "callout",
                "style": "info",
                "html": "<strong>Manager tip:</strong> Pair this course with a local checklist for tools, passwords, schedule, and first-week meetings."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "first-week-success",
            "title": "First-Week Success Checklist",
            "order": 2,
            "estMin": 10,
            "blocks": [
              {
                "id": "text",
                "type": "text",
                "html": "<p>A strong first week gives the employee a map. Confirm the role, reporting line, required tools, safety expectations, training plan, and first deliverables.</p><ul><li>Know who to contact for support.</li><li>Understand daily attendance and communication rules.</li><li>Review required policies and training assignments.</li><li>Ask questions early instead of guessing.</li></ul>",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "quiz",
                "type": "quiz",
                "mode": "single",
                "question": "What is the best first-week practice for a new employee?",
                "required": true,
                "choices": [
                  {"id": "a", "text": "Wait until the end of the month to ask questions", "correct": false},
                  {"id": "b", "text": "Clarify expectations, tools, contacts, and training early", "correct": true},
                  {"id": "c", "text": "Avoid manager check-ins", "correct": false}
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "workplace-expectations",
        "title": "Professional Expectations",
        "order": 2,
        "estMin": 25,
        "lessons": [
          {
            "id": "conduct-communication",
            "title": "Professional Conduct and Communication",
            "order": 1,
            "estMin": 15,
            "blocks": [
              {
                "id": "text",
                "type": "text",
                "html": "<p>Professional communication should be clear, respectful, timely, and documented when needed. Employees should use approved channels and avoid sharing sensitive information casually.</p>",
                "required": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "course-summary",
            "title": "Course Summary",
            "order": 2,
            "estMin": 10,
            "blocks": [
              {
                "id": "summary",
                "type": "callout",
                "style": "success",
                "html": "<p>You are ready to begin with a clearer understanding of culture, conduct, first-week priorities, and support channels.</p>",
                "required": true
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
